---
import LegalLayout from '../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
---

<LegalLayout title="Trademark Policy">
  <div class="max-xl:mx-auto max-xl:w-full max-xl:max-w-(--breakpoint-md)">
    <div class="mt-16 px-4 font-mono text-sm/7 font-medium tracking-widest text-gray-500 uppercase lg:px-2">Last updated: April 9, 2026</div>

    <div class="mb-6 px-4 lg:px-2 xl:mb-16 relative before:absolute before:top-0 before:h-px before:w-[200vw] before:bg-gray-950/5 dark:before:bg-white/10 before:-left-[100vw] after:absolute after:bottom-0 after:h-px after:w-[200vw] after:bg-gray-950/5 dark:after:bg-white/10 after:-left-[100vw]">
      <h1 class="inline-block max-w-(--breakpoint-md) text-[2.5rem]/10 tracking-tight text-pretty text-gray-950 max-lg:font-medium lg:text-6xl dark:text-gray-200">Trademark Policy</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="max-xl:mx-auto max-xl:w-full max-xl:max-w-(--breakpoint-md)">
    <div class="px-4 py-2 lg:px-2 relative before:absolute before:top-0 before:h-px before:w-[200vw] before:bg-gray-950/5 dark:before:bg-white/10 before:-left-[100vw] after:absolute after:bottom-0 after:h-px after:w-[200vw] after:bg-gray-950/5 dark:after:bg-white/10 after:-left-[100vw]">
      <article class="prose prose-lg prose-slate dark:prose-invert max-w-(--breakpoint-md)">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>This Trademark Policy describes the proper use of the "Zod" name, logo, and related trademarks. While the Zod software is available under an open-source license, the trademarks associated with Zod are protected to ensure that the Zod brand remains a reliable indicator of quality and origin.</p>

        <h2>Trademarks Covered</h2>
        <p>This policy covers the following trademarks:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>"Zod"</strong> — the primary project name</li>
          <li><strong>The Zod logo</strong> — including any official variations</li>
          <li><strong>Related branding elements</strong> — slogans, icons, and other visual identifiers associated with the project</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Permitted Uses</h2>
        <p>You may use the Zod trademarks in the following circumstances without prior written permission:</p>

        <h3>1. Referring to the Software</h3>
        <p>You may use the "Zod" name to accurately refer to the software. For example:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>"This project is built using Zod"</li>
          <li>"Powered by Zod"</li>
          <li>"A Zod-based AI agent platform"</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>2. Community and Educational Content</h3>
        <p>You may use the trademarks in blog posts, tutorials, videos, presentations, and other educational or community content that discusses or demonstrates the Zod software.</p>

        <h3>3. Open-Source Contributions</h3>
        <p>You may use the trademarks in forks or modified versions of the software, provided you clearly indicate that your version is a modification and not the official Zod project.</p>

        <h2>Prohibited Uses</h2>
        <p>The following uses are <strong>not permitted</strong> without prior written consent:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Using "Zod" or any confusingly similar name as part of your own product, service, or project name</li>
          <li>Using the Zod logo on your website, marketing materials, or products in a way that suggests official partnership, sponsorship, or endorsement</li>
          <li>Registering "Zod" or any variation as a trademark, domain name, or social media account</li>
          <li>Using Zod trademarks in a way that is misleading, confusing, or disparaging</li>
          <li>Combining Zod trademarks with other logos, symbols, or design elements in a way that creates a new brand identity</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Guidelines for Proper Use</h2>
        <p>When using the Zod trademarks, please follow these guidelines:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Use the trademarks as adjectives, not nouns or verbs (e.g., "Zod software" not "Zod")</li>
          <li>Do not modify, distort, or alter the Zod logo</li>
          <li>Do not use the trademarks in a way that implies endorsement by the Zod project</li>
          <li>Include appropriate attribution notices when feasible</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Derivative Works</h2>
        <p>While the Zod software is open-source and you are free to create and distribute derivative works of the code, the Zod trademarks do not extend to such derivative works. If you distribute a modified version, you should use a different name and branding to avoid confusion with the official project.</p>

        <h2>Enforcement</h2>
        <p>We reserve the right to enforce this Trademark Policy to protect the Zod brand. If we become aware of misuse, we may contact the party involved and request that they bring their use into compliance. In cases of persistent or egregious misuse, we may pursue legal remedies.</p>

        <h2>Requesting Permission</h2>
        <p>If you would like to use the Zod trademarks in a way not covered by this policy, or if you have questions about a specific use case, please contact us at <a href="mailto:trademarks@zod.dev" class="text-sky-500 hover:text-sky-600 dark:text-sky-400">trademarks@zod.dev</a>. We will review your request and respond within a reasonable time.</p>

        <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>We may update this Trademark Policy from time to time. Changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</LegalLayout>
